FL,435,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F434A1773245481
OL,3,CVictory for 'people power' as lido
OL,4,Cprepares to open
OL,6,FAfter listening to the concerns of
OL,7,Fcampaigners about the impact of
OL,8,Fclosure, the council's executive
OL,9,Fcommittee agreed to reverse its
OL,10,Fdecision and reopen the lido this
OL,11,Fseason.
OL,13,FTeignbridge District Council said it
OL,14,Fwill operate the pool this summer
OL,15,Fwhile working with community groups on
OL,16,Fplans for the future.
OL,18,FRichard Keeling, leader of Teignbridge
OL,19,FDistrict Council, said the authority
OL,20,Fhad "listened" to public opinion.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,435,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F434A1773245481
OL,3,CVictory for 'people power' as lido
OL,4,Cprepares to open
OL,6,F"It allows the community to keep using
OL,7,Fthe pool while Teignbridge works with
OL,8,Fthose who are looking towards its long-
OL,9,Fterm future," Teignbridge District
OL,10,FCouncil Deputy Leader, David
OL,11,FPalethorpe, added.
OL,13,FCampaigner Catherine Brown said: "This
OL,14,Fis a brilliant outcome. It's
OL,15,Funbelievable that the council has gone
OL,16,Ffrom a unanimous decision to close it
OL,17,Fto a unanimous decision to keep it
OL,18,Fopen!
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,435,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F434A1773245481
OL,3,CVictory for 'people power' as lido
OL,4,Cprepares to open
OL,6,F"It shows that people power does
OL,7,Fmatter. The council has listened, and
OL,8,Fthat's brilliant. We are very grateful
OL,9,Fto them."
OL,11,FBuilt in the 1970s, Teignmouth Lido
OL,12,Ffeatures a 25m pool which is usually
OL,13,Fopen from May to September.
OL,15,FThe lido was closed for three years
OL,16,Ffor #800,000 of renovation work and
OL,17,Freopened in May 2023.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,435,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F434A1773245481
OL,3,CVictory for 'people power' as lido
OL,4,Cprepares to open
OL,6,FAhead of the vote, the council's
OL,7,Fexecutive heard it would cost the
OL,8,Fcouncil #74,000 to keep the pool open
OL,9,Ffor the summer, but members were urged
OL,10,Fto think of the value of doing it
OL,11,Frather than the price.
OL,13,FSpeaking after the decision,
OL,14,FTeignmouth town councillor Penelope
OL,15,FLloyd said it was exactly the outcome
OL,16,Fthe town had been hoping for.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
